From f361ed31af54bfd6467f7f0a6282f8c62b0445ef Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: srtlab <gomezsteve1379@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 15:11:28 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 14/20] Fix engParseRfh Gen1 SEC16 offset (0x0226 -> 0x00AE);
 reconcile with engine
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Delegation-discipline proof for the RFH-source sync path found a real bug:
engParseRfh read Gen1 SEC16 at 0x0226 (the key-table / CHAR_MASTER region),
while parseModule, securityBytes.writeRfhSec16Gen1 (the WRITER), pairingRepair
and rfhPcmPair all use 0x00AE. So Gen1 RFH sync read the master from a
different offset than the writer writes to — internally inconsistent.

Aligned engParseRfh Gen1 to 0x00AE / 0x00C0. Now ModuleSync's RFH master
matches the engine + writer (proven: Gen2, Gen2-EEE, Gen1 all AGREE), so the
RFH-source actions resolve the same secret everything else does. CI test
imports the real engParseRfh and locks the equivalence. Gen2 path unchanged.

NOTE: 0x00AE is confirmed by 4 modules incl. the writer; a real Gen1 24C16
bench dump would be the final ground-truth confirmation.
---
