From da76c74ee54bf1f7fdad5008ab3cac16bb579774 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: srtlab <gomezsteve1379@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 21:09:02 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 18/20] GPEC immo: surface the SKIM (0x0011) immobilizer enable
 byte
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The GPEC immo analyzer showed VIN + SEC6 + marker but never the SKIM byte
@0x0011 — the immobilizer enable/disable flag (0x80=ENABLED, 0x00/0x02=
DISABLED/bypassed). So a PCM could read SEC6-SET / IMMO-SYNC yet have the immo
BYPASSED and look fully paired. Confirmed on the corpus: several real GPEC2A
dumps are IMMO-SYNC / SEC6-SET but SKIM=0x00 (bypassed).

analyzeGpec2aPcm now returns a skim block, adds SKIM ON/DISABLED to the state
verdict + state.skimEnabled, and emits a WARNING note when bypassed. Read-only:
the immo fix never writes 0x0011 (a real sync leaves it untouched, per the
bench golden). The info already existed in fileUtils/crossValidate; this
surfaces it in the dedicated immo panel. CI test covers 0x80/0x00/0x02.
